{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":934,"text":"To avoid dangerous climate change,"},{"time":3056,"text":"we're going to need\nto cut emissions rapidly."},{"time":6413,"text":"That should be a pretty\nuncontentious statement,"},{"time":9521,"text":"certainly with this audience."},{"time":11401,"text":"But here's something\nthat's slightly more contentious:"},{"time":14349,"text":"it's not going to be enough."},{"time":17249,"text":"We will munch our way through\nour remaining carbon budget"},{"time":21354,"text":"for one and a half degrees"},{"time":22943,"text":"in a few short years,"},{"time":25352,"text":"and the two degree budget"},{"time":26998,"text":"in about two decades."},{"time":29401,"text":"We need to not only cut emissions\nextremely rapidly,"},{"time":33358,"text":"we also need to take carbon dioxide\nout of the atmosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38882,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40062,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41678,"text":"I work assessing a whole range\nof these proposed techniques"},{"time":46447,"text":"to see if they can work."},{"time":48625,"text":"We could use plants to take CO2 out,"},{"time":52010,"text":"and then store it in trees,"},{"time":54278,"text":"in the soil, deep underground\nor in the oceans."},{"time":57857,"text":"We could build large machines,\nso-called artificial trees,"},{"time":62205,"text":"that will scrub CO2 from the air."},{"time":64809,"text":"For these ideas to be feasible,"},{"time":66954,"text":"we need to understand\nwhether they can be applied"},{"time":69821,"text":"at a vast scale in a way that is safe,\neconomic and socially acceptable."},{"time":75878,"text":"All of these ideas come with tradeoffs."},{"time":78576,"text":"None of them are perfect,"},{"time":80453,"text":"but many have potential."},{"time":83187,"text":"It's unlikely that any one of them\nwill solve it on its own."},{"time":86683,"text":"There is no silver bullet,"},{"time":88045,"text":"but potentially together,\nthey may form the silver buckshot"},{"time":91755,"text":"that we need to stop\nclimate change in its tracks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96569,"text":"I'm working independently\non one particular idea"},{"time":100110,"text":"which uses natural gas\nto generate electricity"},{"time":103616,"text":"in a way that takes\ncarbon dioxide out of the air."},{"time":107079,"text":"Huh? How does that work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109345,"text":"So the Origen Power Process\nfeeds natural gas into a fuel cell."},{"time":114441,"text":"About half the chemical energy\nis converted into electricity,"},{"time":118366,"text":"and the remainder into heat,"},{"time":120429,"text":"which is used to break down limestone"},{"time":123095,"text":"into lime and carbon dioxide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125697,"text":"Now at this point, you're probably\nthinking that I'm nuts."},{"time":129833,"text":"It's actually generating carbon dioxide."},{"time":132488,"text":"But the key point is,\nall of the carbon dioxide generated,"},{"time":136227,"text":"both from the fuel cell\nand from the lime kiln, is pure,"},{"time":139910,"text":"and that's really important,"},{"time":141275,"text":"because it means you can\neither use that carbon dioxide"},{"time":143888,"text":"or you can store it away\ndeep underground at low cost."},{"time":148488,"text":"And then the lime that you produce\ncan be used in industrial processes,"},{"time":153733,"text":"and in being used,\nit scrubs CO2 out of the air."},{"time":158002,"text":"Overall, the process is carbon negative."},{"time":160826,"text":"It removes carbon dioxide from the air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164423,"text":"If you normally generate\nelectricity from natural gas,"},{"time":169073,"text":"you emit about 400 grams\nof CO2 into the air"},{"time":172902,"text":"for every kilowatt-hour."},{"time":175127,"text":"With this process,\nthat figure is minus 600."},{"time":181157,"text":"At the moment, power\ngeneration is responsible"},{"time":183902,"text":"for about a quarter\nof all carbon dioxide emissions."},{"time":188643,"text":"Hypothetically, if you replaced\nall power generation with this process,"},{"time":193630,"text":"then you would not only eliminate all\nof the emissions from power generation"},{"time":197594,"text":"but you would start removing emissions\nfrom other sectors as well,"},{"time":201668,"text":"potentially cutting 60 percent\nof overall carbon emissions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206682,"text":"You could even use the lime"},{"time":209252,"text":"to add it directly to seawater\nto counteract ocean acidification,"},{"time":214576,"text":"one of the other issues that is caused\nby CO2 in the atmosphere."},{"time":219910,"text":"In fact, you get more bang for your buck."},{"time":222503,"text":"You absorb about twice as much\ncarbon dioxide when you add it to seawater"},{"time":226802,"text":"as when you use it industrially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229118,"text":"But this is where it gets\nreally complicated."},{"time":231743,"text":"While counteracting ocean\nacidification is a good thing,"},{"time":236158,"text":"we don't fully understand\nwhat the environmental consequences are,"},{"time":240063,"text":"and so we need to assess\nwhether this treatment"},{"time":243317,"text":"is actually better than the disease\nthat it is seeking to cure."},{"time":246865,"text":"We need to put in place\nstep-by-step governance"},{"time":250127,"text":"for experiments to assess this safely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253375,"text":"And the scale:"},{"time":256214,"text":"to avoid dangerous climate change,"},{"time":257868,"text":"we are going to need\nto remove trillions --"},{"time":260971,"text":"and yes, that's trillions with a T --"},{"time":262784,"text":"trillions of tons of carbon dioxide\nfrom the atmosphere in the decades ahead."},{"time":268739,"text":"It will cost a few percent of GDP --\nthink defense-sized expenditure,"},{"time":273958,"text":"lots of industrial activity"},{"time":275948,"text":"and inevitably harmful side effects."},{"time":279085,"text":"But if the scale seems enormous,"},{"time":281176,"text":"it is only because\nof the scale of the problem"},{"time":283726,"text":"that we are seeking to solve."},{"time":285878,"text":"It's enormous as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288923,"text":"We can no longer avoid\nthese thorny issues."},{"time":291963,"text":"We face risks whichever way we turn:"},{"time":294559,"text":"a world changed by climate change"},{"time":296530,"text":"or a world changed by climate change\nand our efforts to counter climate change."},{"time":302656,"text":"Would that it were not so,"},{"time":304012,"text":"but we can no longer afford\nto close our eyes, block our ears,"},{"time":307985,"text":"and say la-la-la."},{"time":309578,"text":"We need to grow up and face\nthe consequences of our actions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313756,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":318901,"text":"Does talk of curing climate change\nundermine the will to cut emissions?"},{"time":325077,"text":"This is a real concern,"},{"time":326938,"text":"so we need to emphasize the paramount\nimportance of reducing emissions"},{"time":331810,"text":"and how speculative these ideas are."},{"time":334340,"text":"But having done so,\nwe still need to examine them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338161,"text":"Can we cure climate change?"},{"time":340706,"text":"I don't know, but we certainly\ncan't if we don't try."},{"time":344729,"text":"We need ambition without arrogance."},{"time":347917,"text":"We need the ambition\nto restore the atmosphere,"},{"time":351212,"text":"to draw down carbon dioxide"},{"time":353054,"text":"back to a level that is compatible\nwith a stable climate and healthy oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358257,"text":"This will be an enormous undertaking."},{"time":360775,"text":"You could describe it\nas a cathedral project."},{"time":364145,"text":"Those involved at the outset"},{"time":366151,"text":"may draft the plans\nand dig the foundations,"},{"time":369531,"text":"but they will not raise the spire\nto its full height."},{"time":372418,"text":"That task, that privilege,"},{"time":374401,"text":"belongs to our descendants."},{"time":376801,"text":"None of us will see that day,\nbut we must start in the hope"},{"time":380245,"text":"that future generations\nwill be able to finish the job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384442,"text":"So, do you want to change the world?"},{"time":388114,"text":"I don't."},{"time":389904,"text":"I do not seek the change the world,"},{"time":392157,"text":"but rather keep it as it's meant to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395641,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396816,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":402096,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thanks. I just want\nto ask you a couple of other questions."},{"time":405702,"text":"Tell us a bit more about this idea\nof putting lime in the ocean."},{"time":409165,"text":"I mean, on the face of it,\nit's pretty compelling --"},{"time":411696,"text":"anti-ocean acidification --"},{"time":413914,"text":"and it absorbs more CO2."},{"time":416573,"text":"You talked about,\nwe need to do an experiment on this."},{"time":419139,"text":"What would a responsible\nexperiment look like?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":421376,"text":"Tim Kruger: So I think you need to do\na series of experiments,"},{"time":424362,"text":"but you need to do them\njust very small stage-by-stage."},{"time":426988,"text":"In the same way,\nwhen you're trialing a new drug,"},{"time":429298,"text":"you wouldn't just go\ninto human trials straight off."},{"time":431808,"text":"You would do a small experiment."},{"time":433780,"text":"And so the first things to do\nare experiments entirely on land,"},{"time":437396,"text":"in special containers,\naway from the environment."},{"time":441002,"text":"And then once you are confident\nthat that can be done safely,"},{"time":444505,"text":"you move to the next stage."},{"time":445860,"text":"If you're not confident, you don't."},{"time":447556,"text":"But step by step."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449260,"text":"CA: And who would fund such experiments?"},{"time":451638,"text":"Because they kind of impact\nthe whole planet at some level."},{"time":455537,"text":"Is that why nothing is happening on this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458087,"text":"TK: So I think you can do small-scale\nexperiments in national waters,"},{"time":461932,"text":"and then it's probably the requirement\nof national funders to do that."},{"time":467001,"text":"But ultimately, if you wanted\nto counter ocean acidification in this way"},{"time":472077,"text":"on a global scale,"},{"time":473572,"text":"you would need to do it\nin international waters,"},{"time":475850,"text":"and then you would need to have\nan international community working on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479594,"text":"CA: Even in national waters,\nyou know, the ocean's all connected."},{"time":482671,"text":"That lime is going to get out there."},{"time":484412,"text":"And people feel outraged\nabout doing experiments on the planet,"},{"time":487408,"text":"as we've heard."},{"time":489385,"text":"How do you counter that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491072,"text":"TK: I think you touch on something\nwhich is really important."},{"time":494075,"text":"It's about a social license to operate."},{"time":496515,"text":"And I think it may be\nthat it is impossible to do,"},{"time":500275,"text":"but we need to have the courage to try,"},{"time":502739,"text":"to move this forward,"},{"time":504053,"text":"to see what we can do,"},{"time":505411,"text":"and to engage openly."},{"time":506800,"text":"And we need to engage with people\nin a transparent way."},{"time":509845,"text":"We need to ask them beforehand."},{"time":511875,"text":"And I think if we ask them,"},{"time":513648,"text":"we have to be open to the possibility\nthat the answer will come back,"},{"time":517292,"text":"\"No, don't do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":518920,"text":"CA: Thanks so much.\nThat was really fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521222,"text":"TK: Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}